<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Further Written Evidence Submitted by the Joint Industry Board for the Electrical Contracting Industry to the Communities and Local Government Select Committee Inquiry on Building Regulations Certificati</title></head><body><div><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Further written evidence from the Joint Industry Board (BRC 80)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Summary</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The Joint Industry Board for the Electrical Contracting Industry (JIB) wishes to follow up its initial submission</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> of</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> 5</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> December 2013.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The JIB administers the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Electrotechnical</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> Certification Scheme (ECS) in England, Wales and Northern I</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">reland.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> The JIB is owned jointly by Unite the Union and the Electrical Contractors’ Association.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The ECS is affiliated to the Construction Skills Certification Scheme (CSCS).</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The ECS is </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">currently </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">used</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> predominantly</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> across the industrial and commercial se</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ctors of the electrical contracting industry to accredit the skills and competence of some 100,000 elect</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ricians and related disciplines under the jurisdiction of the JIB.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The JIB </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">offers </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">to extend the reach of the ECS to encompass the domestic sector of th</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">e industry, including work undertaken by individuals whose organisations have registered with a Competent Person Scheme under Part ‘P’ of the Building Regulations.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The JIB wishes to ensure that the well-established arrangements already in place across the</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> industrial and commercial sectors are complemented by the inclusion of the domestic sector, thus introducing common standards of competence across all three sectors.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Proposal</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Arrangements, which predate the introduction of Part ‘P’ of the Building Regula</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">tions in 2005, already exist between the JIB and the following organisations:</span></li></ol><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The National Inspection Council for Electrical Installation Contracting (NICEIC)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The National Association of Professional Inspectors and Testers (NAPIT)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The Electrical Contractor</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">s’ Association (ECA)</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Unde</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">r these arrangements over 2,000 of the total of 100,000</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> E</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">CS cards are held by Qualified Supervisors</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> who work</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">in the domestic sector.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">A number of other ECS card holders also work in the domestic sector. These are electricians and </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">other disciplines who work in the industrial and/or commercial sector but also work from time to time within the domestic sector.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The JIB proposes to develop these existing arrangements to take account of some of the concerns expressed </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">to</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> the Select Commit</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">tee about the competence of electricians and other disciplines who undertake electrical installation and repairs in dwellings.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The JIB offers to engage in early discussions with all the Competent Person Schemes to introduce ECS cards within the domestic se</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ctor. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The benchmark standard which the JIB applies to electricians within the industrial and commercial sectors is NVQ level 3 or equivalent.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> Such individuals qualify for the Installation Electrician ECS card.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The JIB has developed a Domestic Electrician </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">card which </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">also </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">requires NVQ level 3 or equivalent</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> qualification</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> This aligns the card with the NVQ level 3 qualification introduced in April 2013 for all new Qualified Supervisors and will allow the domestic sector to introduce ECS cards for existing Qual</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ified Supervisors and electricians who undertake work which is signed off by a Qualified Supervisor</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Appropriate intermediate ECS cards will be introduced to provide a pathway to the Domestic Electrician card where individuals do not currently qualify for </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">the Domestic Electrician card. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The ECS cards will include a photograph of the card holder </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">it is proposed that it should also display the common registration mark which is being developed to denote registration with a Competent Person Scheme.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The benef</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">its which this will bring include the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">following</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The consumer will benefit from the introduction of the NVQ level 3 standard across the domestic sector, thus ensuring that work is executed to the standards which already apply across the industrial and </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">commercial sectors</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">improvi</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ng</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> standards of safety and workmanship.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The individuals who work in the domestic sector will benefit by their inclusion in the industry’s skills accreditation scheme, thus providing them with the opportunity to broaden and expan</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">d their skills and further their careers</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The industry will benefit by the introduction of common standards of com</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">petence across the industrial, commercial and domestic sectors.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="17" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The scope of work of a Domestic Electrician differs from that of the electri</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">cian who works in the industrial and commercial sectors. If a </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Domestic Electrician</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> wishes to undertake work in the industrial and commercial sector they will be </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">able</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> to undertake further training to allow them to qualify for the Installation Electrician ca</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">rd.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="18" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">he JIB </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">offers to</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> work with the Competent Person Schemes to introduc</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">e a procedure </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">to address </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">substandard work under</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">taken by a card holder. Complaints may be registered by the consumer or</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> ECS card holders </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">who</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">undertake </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">further</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> work at the consumer’s dwelling. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Appropriate measures will be introduced by the JIB in conjunction with the Competent Person Schemes to address </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">any </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">substandard work.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Conclusion</span></p><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">This offer is intended to address the concerns expressed to the Select Commit</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">tee, as follows:</span></li></ol><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The introduction of the Domestic Electrician card will drive up standards across the domestic sector to match those which have been established for many years in the industrial </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">amd</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> commercial sectors</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The existing well established arrangeme</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">nts in the industrial and commercial sectors will be retained and enhanced by the introduction of complementary measures in the domestic sector and will lead to the more efficient deployment of valuable skills across the whole sector</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The standard of electr</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ical installation and repair in dwellings will be lifted to the levels which apply in the industrial and commercial sectors, thus enhancing standards of electrical safety and the quality of work.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The industry will be more coherent</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">more professional and</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> this will allow the consumer to have full confidence in the quality of electrical work undertaken in their home.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-st